.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-PREFLIGHT" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.16" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-preflight \- Check cluster prerequisites on the submission host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose preflight [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Check whether the submission host and compose specification satisfy the prerequisites for a later submit. This validates required binaries, cache path safety, local mounts, and Pyxis or Slurm availability.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read. Default: compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--strict\fR
Treat warnings as failures.
.TP
\fB--verbose\fR
Show detailed preflight findings.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--enroot\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the enroot executable. Default: enroot.
.TP
\fB--sbatch\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sbatch executable. Default: sbatch.
.TP
\fB--srun\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the srun executable. Default: srun.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose preflight \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose preflight \-f compose.yaml \-\-strict
hpc\-compose preflight \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
